/span> : <span class=\"fn\">F</span>), <span class=\"fn\">∀ <span class=\"fn\">x</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Interval/Set/UnorderedInterval.html#Set.uIcc\">Set.uIcc</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span>, <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `f` is absolutely continuous on `uIcc a b` and `f' x = 0` for a.e. `x ∈ uIcc a b`, then `f`\nis constant on `uIcc a b`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/AbsolutelyContinuousFun.html#AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval.const_of_ae_hasDerivAt_zero","kind":"theorem","line":164,"name":"AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval.const_of_ae_hasDerivAt_zero","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/AbsolutelyContinuousFun.lean#L164-L218"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/AbsolutelyContinuousFun.html#AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval.dist_le_of_pairwiseDisjoint_hasSum\"><span class=\"name\">AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval</span>.<span class=\"name\">dist_le_of_pairwiseDisjoint_hasSum</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#PseudoMetricSpace\">PseudoMetricSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\".