 : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">u</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Pairwise/Basic.html#Set.PairwiseDisjoint\">PairwiseDisjoint</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">z</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Interval/Set/Defs.html#Set.Icc\">Set.Icc</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">z</span>.1</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">z</span>.2</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hu₃</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/InfiniteSum/Defs.html#HasSum\">HasSum</a> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">z</span> : <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">u</span></span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(↑<span class=\"fn\">z</span>)</span>.2</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(↑<span class=\"fn\">z</span>)</span>.1</span>)</span> (<span class=\"fn\">b</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hu₄</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/InfiniteSum/Defs.html#HasSum\">HasSum</a> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">z</span> : <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">u</span></span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#Dist.dist\">dist</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(↑<span class=\"fn\">z</span>)</span>.1</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(↑<span class=\"fn\">z</span>)</span>.2</span>)</span></span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">y</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#Dist.dist\">dist</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">y</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `f` is absolutely continuous on `[d, b]` and there is a collection of pairwise disjoint\nclosed subintervals of `(d, b)` of total length `b - d` such that the sum of `dist (f x) (f y)` for\n`[x, y]` in the collection is equal to `y`, then `dist (f b) (f d) ≤ y`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/AbsolutelyContinuousFun.html#AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval.dist_le_of_pairwiseDisjoint_hasSum","kind":"theorem","line":103,"name":"AbsolutelyContinuousOnInterval.dist_le_of_pairwiseDisjoint_hasSum","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/AbsolutelyContinuousFun.lean#L103-L162"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/AbsolutelyContinuousFun.html#exists_dist_slope_lt_pairwiseDisjoint_hasSum\"><span class=\"name\">exists_dist_slope_lt_pairwiseDisjoint_hasSum</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">f </span><span class=\"fn\">f'</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> → <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">d </span><span class=\"fn\">b </span><span class=\"fn\">η</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hdb</span> : <span class=\"fn\">d</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hf</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">∀ᵐ</a> (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>)<a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Interval/Set/Defs.html#Set.Ioo\">Set.Ioo</a> <span class=\"fn\">d</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/Deriv/Basic.html#HasDerivAt\">HasDerivAt</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f'</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hη</span> : <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">η</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">u</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> (<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>)</span>),\n  <span class=\"fn\">(∀ <span class=\"fn\">z</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">u</span>, (<span class=\"fn\">d</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">z</span>.1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">z</span>.1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">z</span>.2</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">z</span>.2</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span>) <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Pseudo/Defs.html#Dist.dist\">dist</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Slope.html#slope\">slope</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">z</span>.1</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">z</span>.2</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f'</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">z</span>.1</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">η</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a>     <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">u</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Pairwise/Basic.html#Set.PairwiseDisjoint\">PairwiseDisjoint</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">z</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Interval/Set/Defs.html#Set.Icc\">Set.Icc</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">z</span>.1</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">z</span>.2</span></span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/InfiniteSum/Defs.html#HasSum\">HasSum</a> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">z</span> : <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">u</span></span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(↑<span class=\"fn\">z</span>)</span>.2</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(↑<span class=\"fn\">z</span>)</span>.1</span>)</span> (<span class=\"fn\">b</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `f` has derivative `f'` a.e. on `[d, b]` and `η` is positive, then there is a collection of\npairwise disjoint closed subintervals of `[a, b]` of total length `b - a` where the slope of `f`\non each subinterval `[x, y]` differs from `f' x` by at most `η`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/AbsolutelyContinuousFun.html#exists_dist_slope_lt_pairwiseDisjoint_hasSum","kind":"theorem","line":38,"name":"exists_dist_slope_lt_pairwiseDisjoint_hasSum","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral/AbsolutelyContinuousFun.lean#L38-L101"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Algebra.BigOperators.Group.Finset.Gaps","Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.Deriv.Mul","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.IntervalIntegral.DerivIntegrable","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.IntervalIntegral.LebesgueDifferentiationThm"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.IntervalIntegral.AbsolutelyContinuousFun"}